<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Anonymous on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/anonymous/</link><description>Recent content in Anonymous on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/anonymous/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] MATLAB Invalid Function Handle</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/matlab/matlab-invalid-function-handle/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/matlab/matlab-invalid-function-handle/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A function handle in MATLAB is created with &lt;code&gt;@&lt;/code&gt;. &amp;ldquo;Invalid function handle&amp;rdquo; occurs when the referenced function doesn&amp;rsquo;t exist, the syntax is wrong, or the handle is corrupted.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Typo in function name after @&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Function not on MATLAB path&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Missing @ symbol&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Anonymous function syntax error&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Function handle variable overwritten&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-matlab" data-lang="matlab"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% WRONG: Typo in function name&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;f = @sinx; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% Invalid function handle&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% CORRECT: Use correct function name&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;f = @sin;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;result = f(pi&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% 1&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-matlab" data-lang="matlab"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% WRONG: Anonymous function syntax&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;f = @(x) x &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; ; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% Syntax error&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% CORRECT: Complete expression&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;f = @(x) x &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;f(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% 6&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-matlab" data-lang="matlab"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;f = @nonexistent; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% Invalid function handle&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;g = @(x) x^&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% Valid anonymous function&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;g(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;4&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% 16&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="matlab-undefined-function"&gt;Undefined Function&lt;/a&gt; - function not found&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="matlab-unbalanced-parentheses"&gt;Unbalanced Parentheses&lt;/a&gt; - syntax errors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] MATLAB: Invalid function handle '@'</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/matlab/matlab-invalid-handle-v2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/matlab/matlab-invalid-handle-v2/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;MATLAB errors &amp;ldquo;Invalid function handle&amp;rdquo; when you try to call a function handle that doesn&amp;rsquo;t point to a valid function. This can happen with typos, missing functions, or incorrect anonymous function syntax.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Typo in function name&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Function not on path&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Incorrect anonymous function syntax&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Function handle created from non-function&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Variable shadowing function name&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-matlab" data-lang="matlab"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% WRONG: Typo in function name&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;f = @myFunctin; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% Error: Invalid function handle&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% CORRECT: Verify function exists&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;f = @myFunction; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% Must match exact function name&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-matlab" data-lang="matlab"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% WRONG: Anonymous function syntax&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;f = @(x) x &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; ; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% Syntax error in anonymous function&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% CORRECT: Valid anonymous function&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;f = @(x) x &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;result = f(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% Returns 6&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-matlab" data-lang="matlab"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% CORRECT: Verify handle validity&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; isa(f, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;function_handle&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; result = f(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;else&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; error(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;Not a valid function handle&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-matlab" data-lang="matlab"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% CORRECT: Create handles properly&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% Named function handle&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;f = @sin;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% Anonymous function handle&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;g = @(x, y) x^&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; y^&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% Using str2func&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;h = str2func(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;cos&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% Test handles&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;result1 = f(pi&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% 1&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;result2 = g(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;4&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% 25&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;result3 = h(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% 1&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-matlab" data-lang="matlab"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% CORRECT: Check function exists before creating handle&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;funcName = &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;myFunction&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; exist(funcName, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;file&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; f = str2func(funcName);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; result = f(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;else&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; error(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;Function %s not found&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;, funcName);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="matlab-undefined-function-v2"&gt;Undefined Function&lt;/a&gt; - function errors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="matlab-variable-not-found-v2"&gt;Variable Not Found&lt;/a&gt; - scope issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="matlab-insufficient-args-v2"&gt;Insufficient Arguments&lt;/a&gt; - argument errors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] PHP create_function() Deprecated — Use Anonymous Functions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/deprecated/php/create-function/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/deprecated/php/create-function/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-php-create_function-deprecated--use-anonymous-functions"&gt;[Solution] PHP create_function() Deprecated — Use Anonymous Functions&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;create_function()&lt;/code&gt; function was deprecated in PHP 7.2 and removed in PHP 8.0. It was essentially an &lt;code&gt;eval()&lt;/code&gt; wrapper that created a named function at runtime. Modern PHP uses anonymous functions (closures) with the &lt;code&gt;function () {}&lt;/code&gt; syntax, which is cleaner, faster, and more secure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-youll-see"&gt;What You&amp;rsquo;ll See&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On PHP 7.2 through 7.4:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-fallback" data-lang="fallback"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Deprecated: create_function() is deprecated in /path/to/script.php on line X
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;On PHP 8.0+:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>